article.headline: Miami (FL) 79, Lehigh 58
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Jack McClinton scored 21 points to lead Miami past Lehigh 79-58 on Saturday. It was the sixth straight game in which McClinton, the Atlantic Coast Conference scoring leader, has had at least 20 points. He was 7-of-14 from the floor and 4-of-4 from the free-throw line. Jason Mgebroff led Lehigh (4-8) with 12 points, while Jose Olivero added 11. Miami (6-3) was behind as many as 11 points in the first half, but took a 36-33 lead into halftime and never trailed in the second half. Brian Asbury had 18 points for the Hurricanes, including five 3-pointers. Raymond Hicks, starting in place of injured center Anthony King, scored 13 points, while Danis Clemente had a career-high nine assists. Even without King's 9 rebounds a game, Miami beat Lehigh on the boards 33-23.
